<TEXT>
as mikhail s gorbachev made his way 
around poland this week he fell further and further behind 
schedule leaving thousands of people who had been invited to see 
him waiting for hours sometimes in vain 
the soviet leader arrived in the western port city of sczcecin 
on wednesday already an hour behind schedule and by the time he 
reached his first scheduled event a speech at a shipyard he was 
two hours late 
polish authorities anxious to ensure all went smoothly for 
their soviet visitor had seated the workers nearly two hours ahead 
of time so when gorbachev finally arrived the 3000 people in the 
audience were squirming after sitting practically silent on 
backless wooden benches for four hours 
organizers of the trip kept adding events to gorbachevs 
schedule including a visit to a private farm on his way to the 
airport to return to warsaw 
it was nearly midnight when the communist party chief arrived 
back in the capital just about four hours late the delay forced 
cancellation of a special chamber music concert that had been 
arranged for gorbachev and his wife raisa in a palace on the 
outskirts of the capital 
although most of the unannounced stops had been arranged in 
advance with staterun television often set up to record the 
events polish government spokesman jerzy urban attributed the 
delays to what he called gorbachevs extraordinary popularity among 
the polish people 
never before he said had a visitor drawn such crowds or 
generated so much spontaneous joy 
but at all those events reporters were permitted to witness the 
crowds were screened in advance and polish security often checked 
peoples invitations against their identification cards before 
permitting them within sight of the soviet leader 
