<TEXT>
mohammed ali hamadi charged with 
air piracy and murder in the 1985 twa hijacking to beirut said a 
lebanese group called the organization of martyrs paid for his 
visit to islamic holy places in iran 
hamadi a lebanese shiite moslem told the court thursday that 
he visited islamic holy sites at qom and mashhad traveling via 
tehran asked by the judge to give a date for his trip hamadi 
first said he could not remember but later said it could have been 
in 1985 
hamadi has said he spent two years as a fighter with the amal 
militia in beirut but has repeatedly denied being a member of 
hezbollah a radical iranbacked shiite moslem group in lebanon 
the group is believed to be an umbrella organization for 
kidnappers holding foreign hostages in lebanon one of hamadis 
brothers abdulhadi is hezbollahs security chief 
