the document was obtained after west german federal 
investigators asked authorities in lebanon for assistance in their 
investigation of hamadi 
hamadis defense attorneys questioned the value of the document 
as evidence saying it was an unsigned telex with few details 
hamadi also said that he smuggled explosives into west germany 
because he was afraid of committing a sin against islam 
i did not say no because im a moslem and its my duty to obey 
those who are wiser hamadi said referring to a man he said 
ordered him to smuggle liquid explosives into west germany 
the koran says obey allah obey the prophet and obey those who 
give you orders i was afraid of committing a sin if i did not 
accept 
he refused to identify the man who ordered him to smuggle the 
explosives 
on wednesday hamadi admitted bringing explosives into west 
germany on two occasions he was arrested at frankfurt airport in 
january 1987 when liquid explosives were found in his luggage but 
he said he had succeeded in smuggling another shipment a few weeks 
earlier 
in other testimony hamadi said he fought in southern lebanon 
against israeli forces and took part in street battles in beirut 
against government soldiers and christian phalangist militiamen 
in lebanon between 1984 and 1987 
he said he had been wounded in the arm by a bullet in streeting 
fighting in 1985 but could not remember if his arm was still in a 
cast in june when the hijacking took place 
hamadi has testified that he was a member of the shiite moslem 
amal militia from 1980 to 1982 he said he also took part in 
fighting during that period 
he arrived in west germany late in 1982 and applied for 
political asylum but returned to lebanon in november 1984 after 
his request was turned down 
west germany last year rejected a us request for hamadis 
extradition 
a duesseldorf court sentenced one of his brothers abbas ali 
hamadi to 13 years in prison in april for the january 1987 
kidnappings of two west germans in beirut in an attempt to gain 
mohammeds freedom 
the trial is scheduled to continue on tuesday 
