jesse jackson headed south today looking for 
conciliation with michael dukakis as top democrats questioned 
whether president carter was needed to mediate tensions between the 
two camps 
jackson who called on carter to help ease the rift insisted 
thursday we have every reason to seek a bridge spanning 
differences between him and the nomineetobe 
we hope that in the next three or four days that matters will 
be resolved with dukakis forces jackson said no doubt were 
not going to give up on communications 
