name into nomination for vice president 
we have not yet made a decision about all the strategies well 
employ jackson said 
jackson aide brown said today that the campaign has no present 
plans to put jesse jacksons name up for vice president 
the bus caravan aimed at bringing back memories of the civil 
rights era was also headed for louisville ky nashville and 
chattanooga in tennessee before arriving in atlanta on saturday 
the caravan had been billed as a sort of rolling juggernaut 
building steam as it headed south but jackson spent most of 
thursday closeted in his bus or meeting with advisers 
most of the passengers were reporters rather than jackson 
backers there were at least 110 in the press entourage while 
jackson supporters numbered between 30 and 35 
were not picking up passengers were registering jackson 
said because of travel time were not encouraging additional 
passengers 
at a jammed church here thursday night jackson returned to his 
fiery speaking style but focused on efforts to register new voters 
for the fall fight against the likely gop nominee george bush 
were getting ready to send bush back into private life 
jackson said were picking up registrations all the way down the 
line 
