president reagan on friday named howard h 
baker jr former senator and white house chief of staff to the 
foreign intelligence advisory board for a twoyear term 
baker served as both majority leader and minority leader during 
his senate career and was white house chief of staff for 16 months 
before his recent resignation he will succeed albert d wheelon on 
the board 
although reagan leaves office in little more than six months 
some of his appointments to government boards extend into his 
successors administration 
reagan also announced the appointment of tyrus w cobb a member 
of the national security council staff since 1983 as senior 
director of international programs and technology affairs for the 
council 
cobb has been serving as director of soviet west european and 
canadian affairs for the nsc 
