was reported friday 
the action by the writers union amounts to a rehabilitation of 
the popular jewish bard once condemned by the official press as a 
traitor and a drunkard with a pathological lust for money 
the announcement by the official tass news agency called galich 
a talented poet songster and playwright who was unjustly 
vilified 
bureaucrats responsible for culture in the 1970s closed the 
doors to the press and the motion pictures industry before him and 
then hounded him out of the country for what they considered 
seditious writings tass said 
galichs satire about official hypocrisy the apathy of the 
soviet masses and the labor camps that dot the nation made him 
unpopular with authorities but he was a hit among the people who 
listened to his songs on tapes circulated underground and read them 
in books published abroad 
the writers union accusing galich of agitation for the 
emigration of soviet jews to israel expelled him from its ranks 
in january 1972 galich who wrote screenplays in addition to 
songs was also expelled from the soviet cinema workers union 
he left the soviet union in 1974 and died in paris three years 
later 
