the federal government should adopt uniform 
accounting principles to replace some 200 separate antiquated 
systems it now uses and create a chief financial officer to 
oversee the entire financial picture according to a report 
released thursday 
there is a recognition today that most of the governments 
accounting systems are outdated inefficient and ineffective and 
that improvements in financial management are urgently needed 
said the report by the general accounting office congress 
investigative branch 
getting this gao report is really important because it 
confirms our worst fears said rep joseph dioguardi rny who 
says he is the only practicing certified public accountant in 
congress there are so many aspects to what is structurally and 
systemically wrong 
dioguardi and rep larry craig ridaho released the report at 
a news conference the report had been requested by craig the 
ranking republican on the government operations subcommittee on 
commerce consumer and monetary affairs 
among the reports recommendations 
create a federal chief financial officer within the treasury 
department who would have the power to oversee and direct the 
financial management accounting and budget systems of the federal 
government 
prepare audited financial statements every year in every major 
department and agency 
change from the current cashbasis oneyear accounting system 
to a long and short term or accrual system 
adopt uniform accounting systems in every department and major 
agency replacing the more than 200 systems now in use 
weve got to get some better accountability some better 
controls and some better information said frederick d wolf 
director of gaos accounting and financial management division who 
attended the news conference 
