temperature records continue to fall friday in parts of the 
midwest and east and severe storms injured several people damaged 
buildings and knocked out power in the omaha neb area and parts 
of florida and michigan 
by early aftenoon readings passing the century mark were common 
across the arizona and california deserts as well as portions of 
illinois kansas missouri south carolina and west virginia 
the temperature reached 102 in chicago on friday beating an 
11yearold record by 3 degrees another record fell there too it 
was the fifth time this year that temperatures had reached triple 
digits in the windy city more than any other year on record 
in pittsburgh the thermometer reached 91 degrees by early 
afternoon to make the 12th consecutive day of 90 degree or greater 
temperatures this equals the record string of 90degree days set 
in july 1881 
other temperature records were set in eau claire wis 101 
besting the 1936 record by 1 degree la crosse wis 102 beating 
the 1931 record by 3 degrees madison wis 98 beating the 1901 
record by 2 degrees and rockford ill 101 beating the 1932 
record by 1 degree records were tied in minneapolisst paul 101 
and in cape hatteras nc 90 
in council bluffs iowa thunderstorms packing tornadoes caused 
extensive damage in a residential area at least eight people were 
reported being treated at hospitals at council bluffs officials 
said most of the injuries were described as minor 
strong winds associated with the storms downed trees and broke 
windows and wind and lightning caused scattered power outages 
throughout the omaha metropolitan area of which council bluffs is 
a part a wind gust of 92 mph was reported at omahas eppley 
airfield the weather service reported 
a severe thunderstorm watch continued in effect for parts of 
nebraska south dakota iowa and missouri 
elsewhere heavy rain caused street flooding in parts of the 
florida panhandle early in the afternoon and small trees limbs 
and signs were reported blown down at least two persons were hit 
by lightning 
earlier friday strong thunderstorms sometimes accompanied by 
hail moved through northern wisconsin and the northern half of 
michigan one person suffered a broken leg when thunderstorm winds 
downed a tree in vilas county wis the national weather service 
said 
a waterspout moved onshore at st petersburg beach fla 
causing minor roof damage to one house 
heavier rainfall for the six hours ending at 2 pm edt included 
083 inch at grand island neb 074 inch at green bay wis 058 
inch at gwinn mich 048 inch at hancock mich and 044 inch at 
marquette mich 
temperatures around the nation at 3 pm edt ranged from 61 
degrees at crescent city calif to 106 degrees at glendale ariz 
fridays morning low was 39 degrees at truckee calif and 
missoula mont 
the national weather forecast for saturday called for scattered 
showers and thunderstorms from the central and southern high plains 
through the middle mississippi valley the ohio valley to the 
midatlantic coast the storms will be most numerous across the 
eastern great lakes and new england afternoon showers and 
thunderstorms also were forecast in much of the southeast 
highs above 100 were forecast across missouri and kansas and in 
the desert southwest and interior valleys of california in the 70s 
and 80s from the pacific northwest into western montana and from 
the northern great lakes into new england and in the 90s across 
most of the rest of the nation 
