<TEXT>
an 8yearold boy who had no heartbeat and a 
body temperature of only 70 degrees after spending four hours 
trapped in a freezer died friday 21 hours after he was discovered 
by his father hospital officials said 
although medical personnel had managed to get joseph kroggs 
heart beating and return his body temperature to normal he made no 
further progress said jane yousey spokeswoman for rainbow babies 
and childrens hospital 
he was put on life support and he never regained 
consciousness ms yousey said 
when joseph arrived at st joseph hospital in lorain at 7 pm 
thursday emergency room dr stephen evans told the boys father 
dale krogg the chances of resuscitating him were one in a million 
icicles had formed on his body and his heart had stopped beating 
but doctors began an elaborate process of rewarming josephs 
body by running tubes of warm saline through his stomach and 
bladder and wrapping him in electric blankets 
about 11 pm josephs heart began to beat again and by 1 am 
friday he had a strong pulse and good blood pressure and his 
temperature returned to normal evans said 
the youth was then airlifted 35 miles to rainbow babies and 
childrens hospital in cleveland where he died at 402 pm friday 
the youth was reported missing by his parents around 5 pm 
thursday said detective sgt joe monia of the sheffield lake 
police department his father found him at 630 pm when he went 
to the freezer in the familys garage to get meat for dinner 
joseph had apparently fallen into the freezer while trying to 
reach some popsicles monia said a discarded battery had been 
pushed in front of the freezer to act as a step for the youth he 
said 
it appears he crawled up on the battery and tumbled in 
monia said the lid closed on him and latched 
because of the location of the freezer any pounding or yelling 
would not be heard by anyone the father said 
evans said doctors believed it a miracle the boy survived as 
long as he did 
while some drowning victims have revived after up to an hour in 
similar freezing conditions said evans weve never had anyone 
survive so long this is what makes it so unusual 
</TEXT>
