<TEXT>
police say a routine licenseplate check 
led to the arrest of five alleged members of a violent polygamist 
sect linked to killings in utah texas and other states 
the five people in custody in phoenix were identified this week 
as children or followers of the late polygamist cult leader ervil 
lebaron authorities were still seeking at least seven other 
alleged members of the cult 
ervils son heber lebaron 27 and four people described as 
hebers siblings or half siblings were arrested july 1 on 
investigation of auto theft charges after a stolen truck was found 
at a phoenix motel at which they were staying 
authorities at first released three of the five on bail before 
realizing through fingerprint checks and other clues that the five 
were linked to the cult the three were then rearrested 
all had given false names and dates of birth said sgt andy 
anderson chief spokesman for the phoenix police department 
there was no evidence at the time to hold them said 
anderson there was no connection to the lebaron cult until 
wednesday 
anderson said the initial arrests were triggered when a police 
sergeant running license checks july 1 on vehicles in a motel 
parking lot found a pickup truck reported stolen in texas 
heber lebaron and two of his half brothers who are still at 
large aaron and andrew lebaron are wanted for questioning in the 
june 27 executionstyle slayings in texas of three men and an 
8yearold girl 
some of the cult members are also wanted for questioning in an 
october 1987 killing in utah authorities said 
of course were glad but were not totally relieved until the 
others are arrested too said thelma chynoweth mother of two 
of the texas victims and grandmother of the 8yearold girl she is 
also the grandmother of aaron and andrew lebaron in the groups 
complicated poligamybased family tree 
the senior lebaron 56 died in 1981 of a heart attack at the 
utah state prison he had been sentenced to a life term for 
masterminding the 1977 gunshot slaying of a rival polygamist 
although the utahbased church of jesus christ of latterday 
saints now excommunicates those who advocate or practice polygamy 
authorities estimate that 20000 to 30000 people live a 
religionbased polygamist lifestyle in utah and neighboring states 
observers of the lebaron cult have said the group believes in 
blood atonement or the killing of members who have left the 
group 
the oct 16 1987 slaying in utah of daniel ben jordan 53 of 
bennett colo and the june 27 killings in texas of duane 
chynoweth 31 his daughter jennifer 8 his brother mark 36 
and eddie marston 32 brought to 18 the number of ervil lebarons 
former disciples family members and critics who have died or 
disappeared in the last 22 years from utah to mexico 
none of those in custody has been charged in the recent 
killingsthe five were charged with operating an illegal enterprise 
and are believed to have run an autotheft ring in the phoenix area 
for several months anderson said 
heber lebaron also is being held on an aggravated robbery charge 
stemming from a richardson texas savings and loan robbery 
another suspect identified through fingerprints as douglas 
barlow 28 also faces a houston charge of burglary out of an auto 
police said 
