<TEXT>
eleven of the skeletons each had a 
bullet hole in the skull some with mouths agape as if in a shriek 
a few still had on shreds of the clothing they wore in their last 
living moment 
in a walledoff tenniscourtsized section of avellaneda 
municipal cemetery is a burial ground that authorities believe 
contains the remains of 200 to 300 victims of argentinas dirty 
war of the 1970s when a military dictatorship ruled argentina 
the mass gravesite in this industrial city of 650000 southeast 
of buenos aires is the largest so far found of those believed slain 
by 1970s security forces hunting down subversives 
each weekday six young forensic anthropologists unearth more 
bones in an attempt to document what happened to those victims 95 
percent of whom bear evidence of having been shot in the head from 
shortrange at the peak of the repression in 197678 
most of the victims are of our own generation said the 
teams leader 30yearold morris tidball binz we even found the 
remains of one woman who was 76 its hard to figure out who she 
was a threat to 
the four men and two women of the argentine forensic 
anthropology team have uncovered 83 victims in the four years 
theyve been working together through identifications of 20 of 
those victims three military officers have been convicted of 
homicide or kidnapping 
a government panel created by president raul alfonsin identified 
8961 people who died during those years although human rights 
groups say the number who were abducted vanished and now are 
presumed dead is about 20000 
building legal cases against the killers is one of the goals of 
the team another is documenting what happened in those bloody 
years when scores of suspected leftists data shows half were 
laborers or students disappeared most at night and most 
from their own homes 
most were taken by security men to one of the 340 detention 
centers for questioning many were tortured often fatally 
evidence indicates some were dumped from airplanes into the river 
plate estuary others were tossed in unmarked graves that came to 
be called nn or noname graves 
its not pretty said luis fondebrider at 24 the youngest 
member of the team were trying to piece together what happened 
for historys sake so that hopefully it will never occur again 
the team has no government funding a surprise considering that 
alfonsin a civilian who took over the presidency after the 
military stepped down is a human rights activist who ordered 
trials that convicted five military junta leaders including two 
expresidents 
the team receives 48000 in funding from the new yorkbased 
ford foundation the mitterrand foundation of france and the us 
world council of churches its members take public transportation 
to work and share office space with a human rights group in an old 
threestory building near downtown buenos aires 
the team began in 1984 when tidball binz then a medical 
student was recruited by the renowned forensic anthropologist 
clyde snow of norman okla to help the newly restored democracy 
identify the remains of some dirtywar victims 
five of tidball binzs companions joined the team 
its work involves meticulously excavating a skeleton measuring 
bones making xrays examining dental records and comparing every 
bit to information from the medical charts of the missing their 
findings are entered into a computer 
finding one that matches dental records often horrifies the 
victims relatives 
it is still very very traumatic for the families of the 
victims some even continue denying it the body is who it is 
despite the proof tidball binz said 
whats found in the graves which snow calls a time capsule 
that preserves proof of the identity and cause of death have 
proven damning to those who contended the victims died in gunfights 
with security forces 
in nearly every case uncovered by the team evidence showed they 
had been slain with a shot to the base of the skull from about 
three feet away 
in many cases fragments of bullets from standard policeissue 
shotguns were found in the skull tidball binz said a few cases 
showed victims were pregnant or recently gave birth some burial 
plots contained groupings of choppedoff hands 
