<TEXT>
like a casino player fingering the chips in his 
pocket corporate raider carl c icahn is likely to wait awhile 
before he walks up to the window and cashes in his texaco inc 
stock for a multimilliondollar prize 
the beleagured oil giants largest shareholder and most vocal 
critic is just days away from being able to sell his roughly 36 
million shares and keep the profits 
but will he 
speaking from his new offices in mount kisco ny icahn said 
that at this point we havent made any decision yet about the 
148 percent texaco stake 
he noted there is a myriad of possibilities including doing 
nothing and weve made no determination of what were going to 
do 
under the shortswing profit rule a holder of more than 5 
percent of a companys stock must keep those shares for at least 
six months otherwise any profits revert back to the company that 
period ends wednesday for icahn 
texaco stock traded at just over 45 a share on friday at that 
price icahn has a paper profit of about 410 million based on his 
average purchase price of 34 a share 
wall streeters agree icahn is least likely to just dump the 
shares on the open market considering the depressing effect such a 
move would have on texacos stock price 
the bottom line is that neither texaco nor icahn want to see 
the shares go down said paul ting an analyst at the investment 
firm oppenheimer amp co 
far more handsome would be the sale of icahns shares in a block 
to a third party willing to pay a heftier price at 60 a share 
the price icahn put on the table in his proposed 14 billionplus 
buyout he would reap nearly a billion in profits 
