semifinished metal bound for processing on american mills were 
held within the limits of the us steel quota system for the first 
five months of the year 
may imports totaled 194 million tons compared with 153 
million tons in april and 185 million tons in may 1987 according 
to the american iron and steel institute 
imports of all steel products including semifinshed ordered by 
us producers totaled 905 million tons up from 84 million tons 
in the comparable 1987 period the washingtonbased aisi said 
these figures reinforce the domestic industrys assertion that 
the system of voluntary restraint agreements which has been in 
effect since october 1984 should be extended for at least another 
five years said the aisi said in a printed statement 
the american producers said the quotas program has fallen 
short of its objective for the almost fouryear period of its 
implementation 
