<TEXT>
bond prices edged higher in moderate trading 
friday as investors reacted to a surge in the dollar following the 
governments report that the us trade deficit for may had not 
worsened considerably 
the treasurys bellwether 30year bond rose about point or 
about 250 for every 1000 in face amount its yield which moves 
inversely to its price slipped to 914 percent from 917 percent 
late thursday 
long bond prices made the biggest gains but trading in those 
securities was light said william sullivan jr director of money 
market research for dean witter reynolds inc 
the bond market had been sluggish during the week in 
anticipation of three key economic reports on the trade deficit 
producer prices and industrial production all released friday 
morning 
but all of the reports were about as expected and as a result 
had little impact on bond prices analysts said they said bond 
prices got a push however from the dollars rise in foreign 
exchange markets 
there were really no jolts or surprises as far as the economic 
data sullivan said but the international markets interpreted 
the trade figures very bullishly and the dollar moved up smartly 
the dollars firmer trend helped support higher bond prices 
the commerce department reported the deficit widened to 109 
billion in may from a revised april figure of 103 billion 
analysts had expected the trade gap would expand to the 11 
billion area the 109 billion imbalance was the second lowest in 
almost three years 
the continued improved trend in the trade figures and strength 
in the dollar as a result of them have temporarily offset fears of 
higher shortterm interest rates said marshall b front an 
economist at the chicago investment and mutualfund management firm 
of stein roe amp farnham 
a sharp widening of the trade gap in the past has hurt the 
dollar and led to declines in bond prices bond investors fear a 
lower dollar will lead to inflation credittightening by the 
federal reserve and surging interest rates 
a moderate 04 percent rise for june in the governments 
producer price index also boosted investor confidence front said 
bond prices were up modestly reflecting a sense of relief that 
the trade figures and the producer price index didnt provide any 
important shocks and didnt reveal any negatives he said 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
government issues rose about 116 point intermediate maturities 
rose by between point to 732 point and 20year issues were up 
532 point according to the financial information service telerate 
inc 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman daily treasury bond index which measures 
price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with maturities 
of a year or longer was up 161 to 113897 
moodys investment grade corporate bond index which measures 
price movements on 80 corporate bonds with maturities of five years 
or longer rose 065 to 28188 
among taxexempt municipal bonds general obligations were 
unchanged while dollar bonds were up point trading was moderate 
threemonth treasury bills were down 1 basis point to a 
discounted rate of 671 percent for a yield of 691 percent 
sixmonth bills rose 4 basis points to a discounted rate of 705 
percent to yield 740 percent and oneyear bills were unchanged at 
726 percent to yield 777 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discounted rate is the interest rate the market uses to price bills 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks was quoted at 7 1316 percent up from 7 percent late 
thursday 
