gannett co inc said thursday that earnings 
advanced 9 percent in the second quarter thanks in part to a 
favorable change in the companys tax rate 
net income was 975 million compared to 897 million for the 
same period a year ago earnings per share increased to 60 cents 
from 56 cents for the same quarter the year before 
operating revenues advanced 7 percent to 8469 million 
compared to 7898 million 
for the first half of 1988 net income increased 21 percent to 
1715 million operating revenues gained 8 percent to 16 billion 
john j curley president and chief executive officer said 
most gannett units achieved higher earnings despite an uncertain 
economic environment which affected advertising volume 
newspaper operations reported increased earnings in the 
quarter and the trend in outdoor advertising improved broadcasting 
earnings were impacted by weak national sales and the companys 
continuing investment in gtg entertainment 
gannett is a nationwide news and information company that 
publishes 89 daily newspapers including usa today 35 nondaily 
newspapers and usa weekend a newspaper magazine 
the company said ad revenues at usa today advanced 6 percent as 
a result of a rate adjustment paid advertising pages for the 
newspaper declined slightly in the quarter 
it operates 10 television stations 16 radio stations gannett 
news service and the largest outdoor advertising company in north 
america 
