cocacola co reported thursday that its profit 
rose 138 percent in the second quarter from a year earlier led by 
strong sales in europe and the pacific that were helped by the 
weaker dollar 
the beverage maker and distributor said net income increased to 
303 million or 82 cents a share from 2664 million or 70 cents 
a share in the second quarter of 1987 
secondquarter revenue rose 99 percent to 23 billion from 
21 billion a year earlier 
for the first six months of the year cocacolas profit jumped 
137 percent to 5136 million or 139 a share from 4518 
million or 119 a share in the first half of 1987 
revenue for the half expanded 145 percent to 42 billion from 
36 billion 
the excellent secondquarter results reaffirm our expectation 
that 1988 will be another year of strong volume and solid 
doubledigit earnings growth for our company coming on top of a 
record 1987 roberto c goizueta chairman and chief executive 
officer said in a press statement 
our core soft drink business has never been on more solid 
ground by any measure he said we expect the next six months 
to benefit from the strong momentum with which our business is 
moving into the second half of this year 
the company said its worldwide soft drink unit sales increased 5 
percent in the latest quarter and 7 percent in the first six months 
outside the united states secondquarter soft drink volume grew 
an average 5 percent including advances of 8 percent in europe and 
6 percent in the pacific the dollars decline against key foreign 
currencies boosted coke sales by making the product cheaper 
overseas the company said 
us sales in the quarter grew 6 percent including a 9 percent 
rise in shipments of cocacola classic 
